data.name: $FILE_ID
data.comment: {locked} This is the file ID for this localization file. This string value should not be used or translated.

data.name: ie9OrOlderNotSupportedError
data.value: This page does not support Internet Explorer releases older than version 10. Please update your web browser.
data.comment: [Tag:ODSP-SPPPLAT-SPLoader] {Locked}An error to show when the user has IE9, or older, as it is not supported. This shows only in the Technical details of the error page.

data.name: firefox43OrOlderNotSupportedError
data.value: This page does not support Mozilla Firefox releases older than version 44. Please update your web browser.
data.comment: [Tag:ODSP-SPPPLAT-SPLoader] {Locked}An error to show when the user has FF43, or older, as it is not supported. This shows only in the Technical details of the error page.

data.name: platformFailedToLoadError
data.value: Platform failed to load. Id: "{0}", name: "{1}"
data.comment: {Locked}An error to show when the platform component fails to load in the page start. {0} is the platform component id and {1} is the platform component name.

data.name: platformFailedToLoadWithMessageError
data.value: Platform failed to load. Id: "{0}", name: "{1}". Error: {2}
data.comment: [Tag:ODSP-SPPPLAT-SPLoader] {Locked}An error to show when the platform component fails to load in the page start. It includes the error message. {0} is the application id, {1} is the aplication name, {2} is the original error.

data.name: applicationFailedToInitializeError
data.comment: {Locked}An error to show when the applicaiton fails to initialize. The {0} placeholder is the error.

data.name: resourceNotFoundError
data.value: Resource "{0}" not found in loader configuration of manifest for component "{1}" ({2}).
data.comment: {Locked}An error to show when trying to resolve the address of a resource and the resource is not present in the loader config of the manifest. {0} is the resource name, {1} is the component id, {2} is the component alias.

data.name: noFailoverPathError
data.value: Cannot call resolveAddress() on a component with no failover path
data.comment: {Locked}An error to show when the component does not have a failover path property.
